author: Wizard of the Pacific Ocean
text:
Love in all its various forms-be it platonic, romantic, etc, can sometimes find you when you least expect it, and/or stop seeking it out. You deserve love. Even if that love comes from an emotional support animal. 

If you're not safe now, be it due to outside or inside forces, there are people always near by who could help, even if you don't know them yet. Be cautious yet courageous, Traveller, for this may be the beginning of a whole new chapter of your story.
Not the end of it.

And just remember,
Even in the darkest, deepest part of the ocean,
Where you may feel the most alone, hopeless,
There are still beings around you who care for you.
Some may try to lure you in with false light-false hope,
But double check to see if that possible false light is coming from a being who wishes to harm you, because that being-that person could be someone who wants to help. A therapist. A close friend. A partner. Maybe even family if you have a good one.

You may rest here for a short time to gather strength-the darkness of the deep can lead to positive and helpful introspection-but, you cannot stay forever.

There's all kinds of love, happiness, and good memories above the surface. And I believe that you can swim back up there, even if you need help from others to reach it.

It'll be okay.
And it's alright to cry.

Be safe now, Traveller. I know you'll do great. I'm proud of you. <3

-3/18/2021 7:18pm, bottom of the pacific ocean

author: Quentin Keane
text:
This is my second checkpoint, I don't know why it took so long for another one to come my way but here I am, bloodied, beaten, and bruised. Things didn't get better. They've gotten so much worse. God have they gotten worse. One of my best friends moved across the country and won't be back for a long, long time according to them, one of my other best friends, the one I cherished most, turned their back on me and spit in my face when I tried to offer them help in an abusive relationship, and willingly kept taking their poison that was their awful significant other, two of my other friends tried to commit suicide in the same month, I'm about to lose my job because I can't juggle it and school simultaneously, my future remains uncertain and scary in regards to schooling and career, and I'm considering letting my girlfriend who I cherish above all other people and things go so I don't weigh her and her bright future down, she has so much potential and is such an immaculate person with so much talent and drive I don't want to be a burden, and though she'd be deeply wounded if I let her go for such a reason I feel like it would be the right thing to do if I really loved her. Why be a burden on her and her magnificent potential for a good life when I'm not even sure I can provide a decent one for myself? 2021 was supposed to be a fresh new start, a new game, but it just feels like DLC for 2020 to me. Despite all this, I still haven't given up. I'm so tired, so burnt out, so broken at this point, but I don't have it in me to just up and walk away from it all. I guess somehow I'll have to get through all of this, whether I like it or not. Here goes nothing, I guess. 

See you all at the next one. 

01/04/21
Saving....

author: Catcocomics
text:
It seems this save point has not been used in some time.
------------------------------------------------------
My projects have been going fairly well. A month ago, I completed the creation my first ever Minecraft adventure map - Vale of Spirits - and posted it on Planet Minecraft. It was a bit of a two month endeavor to be sure, but even with its low view and download count, I am still somewhat satisfied with it. It's not perfect of course, and there are some minor things I think I would want to have tweaked, but I think it is best left as it is from here on.
I have since taken on a new project and am now creating my very own Minecraft resource pack. I haven't finalized a name for it, and it's nowhere near complete yet, but what I have feels good and hopefully tomorrow I will find it in me to put out a new update for it on Planet Minecraft and change it from "15% complete" to "20% complete".
My progress feels slow, but remains steady. Perhaps I am wrong to compare it to the short yet powerful creative bursts I sometimes receive? It is significantly better than prior years where my interest in a project would cease completely after a week or two.
I wonder how this winter will turn out for me...
------------------------

text:
I guess this is a checkpoint, let me just share a story, maybe my next post will be on my current life checkpoint. 

I remember like it was yesterday... the feeling of being alone always haunted me... but one day a person came to me and said "hey, do you want to join me in my group?" .... I was in shock because never could I have imagine to meet a person quite like him.... he introduced me to two of his friends. --- and ------- .... They both greeted me like as if I was already apart of them. Time passes and we would always have a blast talking to each other. Eventually we all met another person by the name of ---.... he resembled myself when I didn't have anybody to turn to and we all felt like one big happy family. About two years have past and when we all felt like as if we were unseperable, things started to change. We all had life to take care of. Everyday seemed like we were growing apart, as if we were slowly starting to not recognize each other.... I turned to him, my first online friend, and told him, "do you think we will always be friends ---? Even if are worlds apart?" And the words he said to me before everything changed completely.... "of course man, no matter where we are at in this world, nothing will break our friendship" ..... Present day, I look up and hope that maybe one day Ill find him, my dear friend who I felt like he was a brother to me.... I just hope that one day I can find him and my other long lost friends...... 

2009-2012

author: Eelektross Succ
text:
Welp, here I am. This is actually my 5th checkpoint.
I didnt post anything on the others since i wanted to hit up the Chrono Trigger ones first, but I guess i'll talk about my experience with the Donkey Kong franchise...


I've never played DKC2, but I played DKC3 Dixie's Double Trouble for the GBA.
It was my first game, which I got alongside my first console, a Silver GBA, all from my Cousin.

I got a far as the bosses of Cottontop Cove and the Factory World. I didn't understand all the mechanics me playing betwee. 6-8 years old, and never got past them.

My Parents had a breakup when i was around 8 and I was wisked to another state, and me not knowing why i was leaving, couldnt find my GBA (I later learned since my father was being unfaithful, the kids of the other person he had over had stolen my GBA and Charger.)

I never have played another game in the series simply by chance.

However, last year, a friend got me a copy of VBA, and some ROMs for a lot of the games i liked on it.
Among them was DKC3.

It took me for a while to touch the game, but i finally got to it in April of this year.

For those of you who saw my posts in the Chrono Trigger checkpoints know what happned.
I lost my Cousin who gave me my GBA, DKC3, and my Childhood to Covid-19, and I started playing the exact day he passed.

After all the little grieving and stress that happened, I dedicated my time to finishing the game in his honor. And that's exactly what I did: 100% cleared the game alongside Krematoa in a single sitting, in 14 hours.

...And that's my story for Donkey Kong. I'll share this at the checkpoints.
It's 2:22 am EST at the time of writing... and I can only wish you guys the best.
Please stay safe in these hard times... others shouldn't have to suffer the loss of you, especially if your younger. My cousin was in his early 20's when he passed this April... so it can affect younger peeps too.

All of you, please have a good night. Game saved.

author: Joxic
text:
Checkpoint:
The start of the journey as I start with the tune of my childhood, the memories of playing DKC at such a young age overflows me with nostalgia that words cannot express how important song this is to me and many of the other travelers that pass by. Some call it a tune of their childhood, a sanctuary or a place that makes them feel at home but uItimately: It's a special tune that lets us connect with each other even though we'll probably never get to know what everyone looks like.

It reminds me of the simplier times in life, playing DKC with my father at the young age of 6, where has the time gone? Recently, i've learnt how to play this song on piano so I can share to the world this piece as well as allowing me to have a nostalgia trip of playing the game of my childhood. My playtrough has been good in general but just because i'm making a gigantic effort to survive.
I've been having a lot of ideas and crafting recipes and I achieved to organize and execute some of them already so that's nice for me.

My creative and class skills (Bard), are improving with time and i'm starting to make melodies that actually affect other player's stats better.

The effects of Dysphoria and Identity Dissociation curse are slowly wearing off since I have made some work on trying to understand them better.
Borderline Personality Curse is not wearing off, indeed i'm starting to feel comfortable with the other person that habitates my body, we often talk and play together.
My in-game quest companion doesn't seem to mind this other person being with me and even accepts her at some point, so that might be something.

I think that's it for now, i'll be spending some time in this Sanctuary, good luck y'all.

author: Dr. Ravioli
text:
Checkpoint (June 13th, 10:32pm)
Today was my mother's birthday party, however it was a bit rough at times. My social anxiety definitely peaked during that event, and mixed with lack of social interaction during quarantine I got v close to a panic attack. I'm quite proud of myself that I was able to prevent it though. I also had to deal with some deadnaming from family as I'm not out to all of them as trans. However, recently i came out to my cousin who was previously transphobic, but turns out hes really chill. I got to see him again today, which was really nice. I'm really close with him, like I consider him my brother. So I'm really glad he supports me, because I'd hate to lose him. The day might've been tough at some points, but I made it through. I got to run outside with my dog, eat fantastic food my dad made and laugh with family. Even in the bad times, theres always good. You just have to know where to look for it.

author: SunflowerYuki
text:
I made it from the vines in the sky to the seemingly never ending ocean floor. This song always sends me back in time where i was just a kid sitting at that bulky tv excitedly playing this game. Now I'm grown and worried about everything, feeling like life is going too fast and when i hear this song...i long for a childhood i feel was too short, I'd give anything for another day to be able to sit down with my nes and put this game on as if it were the first time. I think we all long to return to when life was simpler and the harsh truth of reality was unknown because now that we reached adulthood...it isn't very appealing anymore, sure we're bigger we make our own rules but the burden of the outside world weighs on our shoulders. We are always asked what we want with our lives when heck i don't even know what i want to do with my life and I'm 25! The constant pressure of making the right decisions in life and hoping that in the end your life was fulfilling and you reached your goals. We may be grown now but we all still have that piece of us that lives in that moment of time when each day was bright and new in the innocent eyes of our younger selves. 

Travel safe my friends, maybe our paths will cross again some day. May each day be a adventure and remember to smile, it's just a cloudy day.

author: bluebear
text:
i love you max. and i really always will. 
im going to move forward now, and do my best
my very best
to be a better human than the day i was before.

someone said that they had "memories worth living to remember"
and it really struck a chord with me.
 i feel that way too. About you. About everyone, about everything. Every moment is precious. Every chance i got to love you matters, even if i am not allowed to say hello to you anymore.

When i think of life like that, i stop seeing every painful memory as loss, or lack, or that ive had a shitty go and theres no way to go upwards from here.
But thats not true.
Every moment counted.
Every breathe, every step every tear, mattered.
Every hello, and each goodbye.

And when i think of it that way, it makes me hopeful for all the things that i am now, and all the things that i am not.
And, for all the things i have yet to discover and become.

I am cherished, i am loved
and i am whole.

and you are too.
thank you so much for all the time you have shared with me. It will always be worth living to remember you in my life.

until next time,
-Me
3/16/20
6:20pm.Usa
No matter what happens, i think we are all going to be okay after all of lifes endeavors settle.

author: OPALpersonal
text:
This is it. You've seen it all. Pewdiepie has left for his expedition of real life. Markiplier currently embarks on his journey with Ethan. You know they'll all be fine. 

Onision is dead and buried, James Charles remains on a shaky throne over cracked support... You've experienced a lifetime of Youtube drama, but you've also experienced the best of times. ASDF Movie, The good Youtube Rewinds, Jacksfilm's YGS 100, it's all under your belt. You've been a true pioneer, a veritable adventurer throughout the Youtube scape. 

From Vaporwave, to Game Grumps compilations. From entire readings of the Bee Movie script, to GMod mashup memes.

And this is your reward.

You stand at the end. The edge of the system. For beyond here, there is nothing. Nothing but that endless ocean, forever out of reach through the haze of green algae and the rocky crags of coral. A peaceful, yet melancholy tune accompanies the void between the realm of content, and the realm of the unknown that stands just inches away. You float here, on the inside, looking out into what else could be.

You contemplate. Would it be worth it to break out? To struggle through the water and make it into the vast, blue emptiness, forever to swim into an oasis of streaming sunlight and gentle music? Or are you content to turn back into the familiar territory, and return to the Guitar Hero Memes and Vinesauce monthlies, the Relaxing Video Game Music mixtapes and perfect game speedruns?

Perhaps, just maybe, it's alright to stay here for a moment. Or for a little while.

To listen to the music, and look outside at what could be , just beyond your realm.

At the edge of the internet.




~You found: Edge 2/4~

author: Marcos Paul Real
text: not really. The youtube algorithm is constantly evolving in terms of what content it prioritizes, which means that sometimes a completely different kind of video to the ones you usually watch will get suggested to you. It's basically a black box. It's machine learning; it works on and refines itself without any human intervention. Google coded it to be this way for two reasons: one, it absolves them of any legal liability (if there were a human moderator manually choosing what videos to show the public, Google would be open to potential lawsuits regarding content censorship or bias), and two, if any information came out about how the algorithm operates, people would exploit it like crazy. If it became known that the algorithm prioritizes videos that meet certain conditions, then every creator would focus on meeting those conditions just to get recommended to more people. So not even Google employees know exactly how it chooses the videos it shows to users. It being AI results in it constantly changing its criteria for videos to recommend, which means that, with time, entirely different videos will fall under the criteria the algorithm has set and we'll be shown things like this.

author: Titans Tracks
text: ¬†@Wesley Elliott¬† You said it! this man went to great lengths just to get his sound the way he wanted it. He genuinely enjoyed what he was creating as a musician, even if he had to work for it. I think anyone can appreciate that kind of commitment to your craft.

author: Wesley Elliott
text:
I've actually heard David Wise elaborate a bit on how he made this track; so much resampling of certain notes was done since the cutoff value (or sustain) of certain notes could only be so long. 

So essentially using the sampling system that the SPC700 provides he was able to take pieces of the sound and loop them for a kind of crazy long cutoff effect, which left room to be able to play those sounds over the samples without having the long cutoff points clash, and without having to ALSO lower the maximum polyphony (which im not 100% was possible at the time) to where the tails ov each note would cut off as another note was played.

Long and short; the sound design behing this is absolutely genious and perfectly utilizes everything the SNES's sound processor was capable of

author: T-Squared
text:
Well, what David Wise, the composer, did was bring the level of composing down to that of what he could create on his synthesizer.

Basically, he didn't compose the song on the synthesizer, then throw it willy-nilly into the game with similar-but-not-same instruments. (Which is probably what cheaper games did, like Jeopardy or Ren & Stimpy or the Madden Football series, giving them a harsh and off-beat sound) 

He took the instrument samples from the synthesizer, and injected them into the game program, so what he heard on the piano was what he heard in game, with very little change.
